The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bangla stutter in chase
                                                   Bangla stutter in chase
                      
	St Georges: Captain Shakib-al Hasan reached five for 70 as Bangladesh closed in on its first overseas series win after West Indies were bowled out for 209 on a rain-hit fourth day of the second Test.               
	At 12 am, Bangladesh were 67/3. Raqibul Hasan (28) and Mohammed Ashraful (3) were at the crease               
	Bangladesh, set a victory target of 215, safely negotiated six overs before lunch as they reached 17 for no loss. Tamim Iqbal was unbeaten on 12 while Imrul Kayes was four not out.         
	Bangladesh are seeking a series sweep following their victory in the opening Test in St Vincent a week ago.           (AP)                                                                                                                   
